,Recommended,323450,14602885,"Posted: 22 February, 2015",all,Matthew Broderick,"Robolaxen here with a quick overview of the current JRPG I've been playing over the last few weeks. The game is called Alphadia Genesis and was published by Kemco Games for the iOS, Android, Wii U and PC. The game is a fairly traditional RPG with with 2D overworld graphics that transition into fully 3D battle graphics. Standard turn-based combat, but has a nice combo system that can reward better XP/Currency/Skill Points depending on how large the combo was at the end of the battle. The game features a world map that done in the classic open world Final Fantasy with the use of airships and boats to get you from point A to point B. The game does feature some voice over work but is currently only in japanese but all text has been translated. The controls are responsive and the game has a fair soundtrack.As for the story it is pretty basic, you are the top swordsman in your kingdom, the King sends you on a mission to investigate a murder in a nearby town, you sister tags along because she is the brains of the operation and you are the brawn. you meet many new characters along the way some of which join your party to help investigate the outbreak of murders across the world.Final thoughts, i enjoy the combat system and the banter between the party members. The graphics and soundtrack could be better, but for a game made for the mobile platforms i feel they are more than adequate. My favorite part of the game is the large amount of hidden chest and secret areas to explore. For modern day gamers i would give this game a 6/10. But if you grew up playing the old NES/SNES/PS1 RPGs like i did, i feel this game would garner a higher rating of 7.5/10"
